--------------------------

Its my first try to port something to pkgsrc, so plz no wonder about some things :)

For the linux-pkgsrc-world, systemd is currently deactivated, plz edited the Makefile
for systemd support.


#Linux problems
textproc/libxslt and graphics/lcms2 with liblzma.la problem under linux, lib64 
directory problem, solution is a symlink from /usr/pkg/luib/liblzma.la to the work dirs.

mkdir /usr/pkgsrc/graphics/lcms2/work/.buildlink/lib64/
ln -s /usr/pkg/lib/liblzma.la /usr/pkgsrc/graphics/lcms2/work/.buildlink/lib64/liblzma.la

mkdir /usr/pkgsrc/textproc/libxslt/work/.buildlink/lib64/
ln -s /usr/pkg/lib/liblzma.la /usr/pkgsrc/textproc/libxslt/work/.buildlink/lib64/liblzma.la

graphics/gdk-pixbuf2/ same
textproc/libcroco/
graphics/librsvg/
x11/gtk2/

same with libexpat.la and libuuid.la with graphics/cairo, graphics/cairo-gobjekts,
devel/pango, liblibXft, graphics/librsvg/, x11/gtk2/, net/avahi

Some linux systems (slackware 14.2 too) has a buggy binutils, so "bmake RC= install clean"
fix the problem
